xbrlcore.xlink
Class Locator

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.xlink.ExtendedLinkElement
      xbrlcore.xlink.Locator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Locator
extends ExtendedLinkElement

This class represents a locator within a linkbase.

A locator can either refer to a concept of a taxonomy or to a resource within another linkbase.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

Method Detail

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
Checks if two locators are equal. This is true if and only if:
- their label attributes are equal
- they are in the same extended link role
- they both refer either to the same concept or the same resource

Overrides:
equals in class ExtendedLinkElement
Parameters:
obj - The object the current Locator is checked against.
Returns:
True if both locators are equal, false otherwise.
